To use BimmerLink with Android Auto, the Android Auto add-on must be unlocked in your Android device’s settings.

"Enhance your driving experience with the Android Auto add-on for BimmerLink. Access your vehicle’s sensor values right on your car’s display, and seamlessly use essential features like controlling the exhaust flap or managing ASD settings — available for cars equipped with these functionalities.
Please note: This option only activates the Android Auto add-on for BimmerLink, not Android Auto itself. Android Auto must already be enabled by BMW, and a Bluetooth OBD adapter is required."

When installing a battery with a higher or lower capacity or when installing an AGM battery instead of a lead-acid battery, coding the new battery with BimmerCode is required before registering it. BimmerCode is available on Google Play.

"The following preconditions have to be met in order to register the battery: - Engine off - Ignition (position 2) on - No errors stored in the engine control unit
Please note that in some cars ignition position 2 has to be turned on by pushing the start button a second time without applying the foot brake or clutch."
